{{Infobox organization | name = Unite4Heritage | native_name = | native_name_lang = | named_after = | image = Unite4Heritage logo.png | image_size = | alt = | caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map2 = | map2_size = | map2_alt = | map2_caption = | formation = {{start date|2015|03|28|df=y}} | founder = [[UNESCO]] Director-General, [[Irina Bokova]] | purpose = to create a global movement to protect and safeguard heritage | website = {{URL|http://www.unite4heritage.org}} }}
'''Unite4Heritage''' is a campaign launched on March 28, 2015 by [[UNESCO]] Director-General, [[Irina Bokova]], aiming to create a global movement "to protect and safeguard heritage in areas where it is threatened by extremists".<ref>{{Cite web|title=#Unite4Heritage campaign launched by UNESCO Director-General in Baghdad|url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/news/1254|website=whc.unesco.org|accessdate=15 May 2015|first=UNESCO|last=Centre}}</ref>
The campaign was triggered by the programmatic [[Destruction of cultural heritage by ISIL|destruction of cultural heritage]] conducted in [[Iraq]] and [[Syria]] by the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] (ISIL) since 2014, in particular after the circulation of videos of looting at [[Mosul Museum]], destruction in the city of [[Nimrud]] and the UNESCO World Heritage site of [[Hatra]]. Irina Bokova called the destructions in Mosul a violation of the [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 2199]],<ref name="news">{{cite web|url=http://www.news.com.au/travel/travel-updates/ancient-artefacts-destroyed-in-iraq/story-e6frfq80-1227241419029|title=Ancient artefacts destroyed in Iraq|publisher=News.com.au|date=27 February 2014|accessdate=15 May 2015}}</ref> and the destruction of Nimrud a [[war crime]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Nimrud: Outcry as IS bulldozers attack ancient Iraq site|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-31760656|accessdate=15 May 2015|work=BBC News|date=6 March 2015}}</ref>
Among the different initiatives to support Unite4Heritage, the campaign #faces4heritage can be mentioned, which invites people to change their profile on social networks to raise awareness about heritage destruction. Faces4heritage is presented on the homepage of Unite4Heritage and has become its most active supporting campaign on Twitter.<ref>{{cite web|title=NodeXL SNA Map and Report|date=10 December 2015|url=https://nodexlgraphgallery.org/Pages/Graph.aspx?graphID=58671|website=nodexlgraphgallery.org|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref> #faces4heritage is run by the UNESCO chair in ICT to develop and promote sustainable tourism in World Heritage Sites, at [[University of Lugano|USI - Università della Svizzera italiana]] (Lugano, Switzerland).
